### 1.4 EQUATIONS OF MOTION (From Variational Principle)

#### Einstein Equations Modified

Varying action w.r.t. $g_{\mu\nu}$:

$$G_{\mu\nu} + \Lambda g_{\mu\nu} = \frac{8\pi G}{c^4}\left[T_{\mu\nu}^{(matter)} + T_{\mu\nu}^{(decoherence)} + T_{\mu\nu}^{(DM)}\right]$$

Where three energy-momentum tensors are:

**$T_{\mu\nu}^{(matter)}$: Ordinary Matter**
$$T_{\mu\nu}^{(matter)} = \left(F_\mu{}^\rho F_{\nu\rho} - \frac{1}{4}g_{\mu\nu}F_{\rho\sigma}F^{\rho\sigma}\right) + (\nabla_\mu \phi \nabla_\nu \phi - \frac{1}{2}g_{\mu\nu}\nabla_\rho\phi\nabla^\rho\phi) + g_{\mu\nu}V(\phi)$$

**$T_{\mu\nu}^{(decoherence)}$: Decoherence Source**
$$T_{\mu\nu}^{(decoherence)} = \left(\nabla_\mu \Psi \nabla_\nu \Psi - \frac{1}{2}g_{\mu\nu}\nabla_\rho\Psi\nabla^\rho\Psi\right) + \frac{1}{2}\xi(\nabla_\mu\nabla_\nu - g_{\mu\nu}\Box)\Psi^2$$
$$+ \chi^2 (\nabla_\rho R_{\alpha\beta\mu\nu})(\nabla^\rho R^{\alpha\beta\mu\nu}) g_{\mu\nu} + \gamma^2(\Box R)(\nabla_\mu\nabla_\nu R) + \delta(R_{\alpha\beta}R^{\alpha\beta})(\partial_\mu\Psi^\dagger\partial_\nu\Psi)$$

**$T_{\mu\nu}^{(DM)}$: Dark Matter Density (Constitutive Relation)**
$$T_{\mu\nu}^{(DM)} = (\rho_d + p_d)u_\mu u_\nu + p_d g_{\mu\nu}$$

Where:
- $\rho_d$ = dark matter energy density (derived below)
- $p_d$ = dark matter pressure (small for CDM)
- $u^\mu$ = 4-velocity

#### Quantum Field Equation

Varying w.r.t. $\Psi^\dagger$:

$$\left[\Box - M^2 - \xi R - \delta R_{\alpha\beta}R^{\alpha\beta} - \frac{\alpha_{QG}}{m_P^2} R_{\mu\nu}T^{\mu\nu}\right]\Psi = 0$$

Near horizon ($r \approx r_s$), this becomes:

$$\left[\Box_{KS} - M_{eff}^2(r)\right]\Psi = 0$$

Where effective mass:
$$M_{eff}^2(r) = M^2 + \xi R(r) + \delta R_{\alpha\beta}R^{\alpha\beta}(r) = M^2 + \frac{6\xi}{r_s^2}(1 - r_s/r)^{-2} + \ldots$$

#### Decoherence Continuity Equation

Define decoherence current:
$$J_\mu^{(dec)} = \left(\frac{dS}{dt}\right) u_\mu$$

Conservation:
$$\nabla_\mu J_\mu^{(dec)} = \sigma(r,t)$$

Where:
$$\frac{dS}{dt} = \frac{k_B}{\hbar} \int d^3x \sqrt{g} \, |\langle \chi(x,t) | i[\hat{H}, \hat{\rho}] | \chi(x,t) \rangle|^2$$

