### How to Distinguish from Alternative Dark Matter Models

| Model | Prediction | Distinguisher |
|---|---|---|
| **WIMPs** | Uniform halo | We predict core concentration |
| **Axions** | No precession | We predict 0.5% S-star precession |
| **MACHOs** | Discrete objects | We predict smooth $\rho \propto 1/r^4$ |
| **MOND/TeVeS** | Different accels | Precision GW tests (LISA) |
| **Fuzzy DM** | Wave-like halo | Different core size |

Our model makes **unique predictions** especially:
1. Strong concentration near SMBHs
2. Specific 1/r⁴ radial profile
3. Particular S-star precession signature
4. Particular GW strain modulation (EMRI)

